
details regarding how to set up and monitor the 'dce-viewer' app

-- conda environments --
    two environments are needed, as conflict between ffmpeg v3 (dce2mkv requirement) and bokeh v2 (modern version)
    1) 'dce-viewer' is main bokeh environment, install bokeh numpy boto3 pandas ipython pyproj ipdb
    2) 'ffmpeg3' is dce2mkv environment, install python=3.6 ffmpeg=3 python-dateutil pytz
    ** install DCEUtils in both environments

-- linux packages --
    sudo apt install nginx
    sudo apt install mkvtoolnix (installs 'mkvmerge' as used by 'dce2mkv')

-- run prod and dev apps --
    * main.py should be identical in prod vs dev (if dev represents most updated version)
    * SDIR and VDIR in config.py should be different in prod vs dev (same comment as above)
    * run prod app as
        - chmod +x Lytx.AML.RussellB/aml/dce-viewer/server/start.sh (if not already done)
        - chmod +x Lytx.AML.RussellB/aml/dce-viewer/server/restart.sh
        - chmod +x Lytx.AML.RussellB/aml/dce-viewer/server/kill.sh
        - ./Lytx.AML.RussellB/aml/dce-viewer/server/restart.sh
        - go to in any browser on VPN, http://10.144.240.35/dce-viewer
    * run dev app as
        - conda activate dce-viewer
        - cd Lytx.AML.RussellB/aml/dce-viewer/
        - bokeh serve dev --allow-websocket-origin=10.144.240.35:5006
        - go to in local browser, http://10.144.240.35:5006/

-- monitor nginx --
    sudo systemctl status nginx

-- monitor dce-viewer app --
    sudo systemctl status dce-viewer
    sudo journalctl -u dce-viewer -n 20